<dl id="n08053b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08053b">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08053b"> 53(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 2 vesanique ) / a) who <font color="green">[experiments]</font> every / idea / b) who hides all</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Imaginons un homme qui exprimerait tout ce qui lui passe par la t&ecirc;te; ce serait un personnage insupportable. Un &ecirc;tre taciturne, h&eacute;sitant, faisant myst&egrave;re de tout, ne serait pas moins insociable. Le contr&ocirc;le de l&apos;inhibition manquerait au premier et l&apos;impulsion dynamog&eacute;nique au second. Au fond, ce seraient deux v&eacute;saniques. <br><font color="green">[Let us imagine a man who expresses everything that passes through his head: nobody could tolerate him. A taciturn person, hesitant, who makes a mystery out of everything, would be no less unsociable. Controlling inhibition would be lacking in the first and a dynamogenic impulsion in the second. In reality, both of them would be mentally unbalanced.]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 189</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
